<subSubSection id="8D9386C8944FFFE11AE2FF6CFB38FECB" pageId="6" pageNumber="263" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="C536D543944FFFE11AE2FF6CFBFDFF03" blockId="6.[151,1437,150,573]" box="[199,1063,187,213]" pageId="6" pageNumber="263">
<emphasis id="F7FD0951944FFFE11AE2FF6CFE94FF03" bold="true" box="[199,334,187,213]" pageId="6" pageNumber="263">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the robust appearance of the species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C536D543944FFFE11AE2FF09FB38FECB" blockId="6.[151,1437,150,573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="263">
<emphasis id="F7FD0951944FFFE11AE2FF09FE15FF2E" bold="true" box="[199,463,222,249]" pageId="6" pageNumber="263">Locality and horizon.</emphasis>
Amber mine located near Noije Bum Village, Tanai Township, Myitkyina District, 
<collectingRegion id="074D1BA1944FFFE11AB2FED4FEF0FECB" box="[151,298,259,285]" country="Myanmar" name="Kachin" pageId="6" pageNumber="263">Kachin State</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="BD9E95D3944FFFE11B10FED4FE7CFECB" box="[309,422,259,285]" name="Myanmar" pageId="6" pageNumber="263">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
; unnamed horizon, mid-Cretaceous, Upper Albian to Lower Cenomanian.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8D9386C8944FFFE11AE2FEF1FBFAFE5C" pageId="6" pageNumber="263" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C536D543944FFFE11AE2FEF1FBFAFE5C" blockId="6.[151,1437,150,573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="263">
<emphasis id="F7FD0951944FFFE11AE2FEF1FE98FE96" bold="true" box="[199,322,294,320]" pageId="6" pageNumber="263">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body approximately 2.1 times as long as wide (versus 2.6 times as long as wide in 
<taxonomicName id="0289AEC0944FFFE11F0DFEF0FF34FEB3" authority="Li &amp; Kundrata &amp; Huang &amp; Cai, 2022" authorityName="Li &amp; Kundrata &amp; Huang &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Artematopodidae" genus="Bipogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="263" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trivialis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="F7FD0951944FFFE11F0DFEF0FF34FEB3" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="263">Bipogonia trivialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="F7FD0951944FFFE11AD3FE9CFE8AFEB3" bold="true" box="[246,336,331,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="263">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="ECCEB42A944FFFE11AD3FE9CFE8AFEB3" box="[246,336,331,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="263" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
). Prosternum moderately broad, about 1.7 times as wide as long (versus 1.2–1.3 times as wide as long in 
<taxonomicName id="0289AEC0944FFFE11AC8FEB8FEB9FE5F" authority="Li &amp; Kundrata &amp; Huang &amp; Cai, 2022" authorityName="Li &amp; Kundrata &amp; Huang &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2022" box="[237,355,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Artematopodidae" genus="Bipogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="263" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trivialis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="F7FD0951944FFFE11AC8FEB8FEB9FE5F" box="[237,355,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="263">B. trivialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="F7FD0951944FFFE11B4FFEB8FE1EFE5F" bold="true" box="[362,452,367,393]" pageId="6" pageNumber="263">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="ECCEB42A944FFFE11B4FFEB8FE1EFE5F" box="[362,452,367,393]" pageId="6" pageNumber="263" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
). Metaventral discrimen (almost) complete (
<figureCitation id="5DB2C9C6944FFFE1199CFEB8FBC9FE5C" box="[953,1043,367,394]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1849,1873]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,597,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-198@6.[151,1436,597,1826]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Details of Bipogonia fortis Li, Kundrata &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP179431, under widefield fluorescence. A, Head and prothorax, dorsal view. B, Head and prothorax, ventral view. C, Elytron, dorsal view. D, Posterior body, ventral view. E, Elytron and hind wing, ventral view. F, Abdominal apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: an, antenna; el, elytron; md, mandible; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; R, radial cell; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 500 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500943" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500943/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="263">Fig. 6D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8D9386C8944FFFE11AE2FE45FB08FDEB" pageId="6" pageNumber="263" type="description">
<paragraph id="C536D543944FFFE11AE2FE45FB08FDEB" blockId="6.[151,1437,150,573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="263">
<emphasis id="F7FD0951944FFFE11AE2FE45FE83FE7A" bold="true" box="[199,345,402,428]" pageId="6" pageNumber="263">Description.</emphasis>
As for the genus, except for the following characters: Body broad, 
<quantity id="027178A6944FFFE11E7BFE45FB6CFE7B" box="[1118,1206,402,429]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="263" unit="mm" value="5.2">5.2 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="027178A6944FFFE11EDAFE45FA8DFE7B" box="[1279,1367,402,429]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="263" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
wide. Prosternum broad. Elytral surface with puncture rows (their number cannot be counted due to visibility problems). Mesocoxal cavities separated by more than two times the shortest diameter of coxal cavity. Metaventral discrimen (almost) complete. Hind wing well-developed. Radial cell moderately elongate, about 2.3 times as long as wide; inner posterobasal angle almost right. Abdominal ventrite 5 about 1.6 times as long as ventrite 4.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
