<subSubSection id="8D9386C8944EFFE01AE2F90DFCB5F87E" pageId="7" pageNumber="264" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C536D543944EFFE01AE2F90DFCB5F87E" blockId="7.[151,1437,1754,1960]" pageId="7" pageNumber="264">
<emphasis id="F7FD0951944EFFE01AE2F90DFEE1F922" bold="true" box="[199,315,1754,1780]" pageId="7" pageNumber="264">Remarks.</emphasis>
Extant 
<taxonomicName id="0289AEC0944EFFE01BA8F90DFD95F922" baseAuthorityName="Lawrence" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[397,591,1754,1780]" class="Insecta" family="Artematopodidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Artematopodidae</taxonomicName>
may display some degree of sexual dimorphism in body robustness, antennal length/serration, or pronotal shape (sinuation of lateral pronotal margin) (
<bibRefCitation id="A118A8B2944EFFE019C5F929FB52F8CE" author="Hopping, R." box="[992,1160,1790,1816]" pageId="7" pageNumber="264" pagination="45 - 48" refId="ref5596" refString="Hopping, R. (1936) A revision of the genus Macropogon Motsch. The Pan-Pacific Entomologist, 12, 45 - 48." type="journal article" year="1936">Hopping 1936</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="A118A8B2944EFFE01EB3F929FAC2F8CE" author="Sakai, M." box="[1174,1304,1790,1816]" pageId="7" pageNumber="264" pagination="51 - 61" refId="ref6593" refString="Sakai, M. (1982) Occurrence of the genus Eurypogon Motschulsky in Japan and Taiwan (Coleoptera: Artematopidae). Transactions of the Shikoku Entomological Society, 16, 51 - 61." type="journal article" year="1982">Sakai 1982</bibRefCitation>
; Lawrence; 2005; 
<bibRefCitation id="A118A8B2944EFFE01AF9F8F5FE49F8EA" author="Yoshitomi, H." box="[220,403,1826,1852]" pageId="7" pageNumber="264" pagination="246 - 248" refId="ref6728" refString="Yoshitomi, H. (2018) Description of the male of Eurypogon jaechi Kundrata, Bocakova, and Bocak (Coleoptera: Artematopodidae). The Coleopterists Bulletin, 72, 246 - 248. https: // doi. org / 10.1649 / 0010 - 065 X- 72.2.246" type="journal article" year="2018">Yoshitomi 2018</bibRefCitation>
). Usually, the body is slightly more thickened in females than males. However, the specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="0289AEC0944EFFE01A93F890FECAF8B6" authorityName="Li, Kundrata &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2022" box="[182,272,1862,1888]" class="Insecta" family="Artematopodidae" genus="Bipogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fortis">
<emphasis id="F7FD0951944EFFE01A93F890FECAF8B6" box="[182,272,1862,1888]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="264">B. fortis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
here is distinctly wider than 
<taxonomicName id="0289AEC0944EFFE01872F890FD17F8B6" authorityName="Li &amp; Kundrata &amp; Huang &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2022" box="[599,717,1862,1888]" class="Insecta" family="Artematopodidae" genus="Bipogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trivialis">
<emphasis id="F7FD0951944EFFE01872F890FD17F8B6" box="[599,717,1862,1888]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="264">B. trivialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Besides, no dimorphic prosternum or metaventral discrimen as seen in our fossils has been reported before. Thus, we believe that 
<taxonomicName id="0289AEC0944EFFE019B6F8BCFC35F852" authorityName="Li, Kundrata &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2022" box="[915,1007,1898,1924]" class="Insecta" family="Artematopodidae" genus="Bipogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fortis">
<emphasis id="F7FD0951944EFFE019B6F8BCFC35F852" box="[915,1007,1898,1924]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="264">B. fortis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is more likely to represent a separate species, rather than a specimen of the opposite sex of 
<taxonomicName id="0289AEC0944EFFE018D7F858FCB2F87E" authorityName="Li &amp; Kundrata &amp; Huang &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2022" box="[754,872,1934,1960]" class="Insecta" family="Artematopodidae" genus="Bipogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trivialis">
<emphasis id="F7FD0951944EFFE018D7F858FCB2F87E" box="[754,872,1934,1960]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="264">B. trivialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
